### GMV Trend Analysis: January to March 2025

#### Key Insight
The GMV experienced a dip in February, with a recovery observed in March, surpassing January's sales volume.

#### Supporting Data
- **January 2025**: $10.00 billion
- **February 2025**: $8.26 billion
- **March 2025**: $10.50 billion

#### Business Context
This trend suggests potential seasonality or external factors affecting sales in February. Identifying these factors could help optimize strategies for future sales dips.

#### Visualization
Here's a line chart showing the GMV trend:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Monthly GMV Trend</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <div style="max-width: 600px; margin: auto;">
        <canvas id="gmvChart"></canvas>
    </div>
    <script>
        const ctx = document.getElementById('gmvChart').getContext('2d');
        const gmvChart = new Chart(ctx, {
            type: 'line',
            data: {
                labels: ['January', 'February', 'March'],
                datasets: [{
                    label: 'GMV (in billion USD)',
                    data: [10.00, 8.26, 10.50],
                    borderColor: 'rgba(75, 192, 192, 1)',
                    backgroundColor: 'rgba(75, 192, 192, 0.2)',
                    fill: true,
                    borderWidth: 2,
                    tension: 0.1
                }]
            },
            options: {
                responsive: true,
                scales: {
                    y: {
                        beginAtZero: true
                    }
                },
                plugins: {
                    legend: {
                        display: true
                    }
                }
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

#### Methodology
The analysis was based on GMV data extracted from the `fact_core_item_local` table for the specified period. Data was aggregated monthly and visualized using Chart.js to convey trends clearly.
